{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Plan: 1. Add backend quality tooling around a single Python toolchain, likely `ruff` for both linting and formatting, with stable config in repo. 2. Expand the root `Makefile` so a clean checkout has obvious `format`, `format-check`, `li...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_22", "text": "Plan:\n1. Add backend quality tooling around a single Python toolchain, likely `ruff` for both linting and formatting, with stable config in repo.\n2. Expand the root `Makefile` so a clean checkout has obvious `format`, `format-check`, `lint`, and `check` entrypoints that cover both stacks.\n3. Add shared editor conventions with a root `.editorconfig` and document the project\u2019s short style rules in `docs/contributing.md`.\n4. Run formatters, lint, tests, and the relevant build to verify the new workflow, then write the required reviewer summary file last.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 47, "prompt_index": 9, "prompt_name": "08 \u2014 Quality Tooling and Shared Conventions", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T22:09:18-07:00"}
