{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Repo quality tooling is in place through [Makefile](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/Makefile), [backend/pyproject.toml](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/pyproject.toml), [.editorconfig](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.editorconfig), an...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_70", "text": "Repo quality tooling is in place through [Makefile](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/Makefile), [backend/pyproject.toml](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/pyproject.toml), [.editorconfig](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.editorconfig), and [docs/contributing.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/contributing.md). Frontend stays on `Prettier` + `ESLint`; backend now uses `Ruff` for both formatting and linting. I also normalized existing backend files so the new Python rules pass cleanly, including the test bootstrap in [backend/tests/conftest.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/tests/conftest.py).\n\nVerification ran through the new command surface: `make help`, `make format`, and `make check`, after installing updated backend requirements. Final results were: backend Ruff pass, backend pytest `11/11` pass, frontend ESLint pass, frontend Vitest `2/2` pass, and frontend production build pass. No browser checks or LLM eval work were applicable for this task. The required reviewer summary is written at [prompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.summary.md). Unrelated prompt-log files already present in the worktree were left untouched.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 137, "prompt_index": 9, "prompt_name": "08 \u2014 Quality Tooling and Shared Conventions", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T22:14:51-07:00"}
